com.opengamma.strata.market.explain

Class ExplainKey<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.collect.type.TypedString<ExplainKey<T>>
      • com.opengamma.strata.market.explain.ExplainKey<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the object associated with the key
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ExplainKey<T>>

    public final class ExplainKey<T>
extends TypedString<ExplainKey<T>>
    A key for the map of explanatory values.

    This key is used with ExplainMap to create a loosely defined data structure that allows an explanation of a calculation to be represented.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public static final ExplainKey<Double> COMBINED_RATE
        The combined rate, including weighting. This rate differs from the observed rate if there is more than one fixing involved. For example, IborInterpolatedRateObservation has two observed rates which are combined to create this rate.
